\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Obo!\u8221\'94 Mandri shouted. \u8220\'93Obo, wake the fuck up!\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 With a jolt, the crack in the floor opened wider, then a thunderous boom sent it shooting across the length of the room, fracturing the chamber in two. The whole left side slid down an inch before coming to a rest on some new foundation of rubble, a, twain.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Mandri, fear pulsing in chest, yanked one of the aged corpses out its resting place and tossed it onto the ground. He then grabbed Obo\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s wrist and threw him into the now unoccupied grave. He pushed the Mazyd as far towards the back as he could, stuffing Obo\u8217\'92s tumbling arms under his body, then Mandri crawled in alongside him. The moment Mandri tucked in his legs, the ceiling started to collapse.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 The first thing to go was the clay oil lamp. It jostled loose from its hook and smashed onto the floor, splashing licks of oil and flame about the room. Then the walls shook, and the seams in the ceiling burst, shooting a jet of smoke into the room, flooding Mandri\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s grave, obscuring the air so completely that Mandri couldn\u8217\'92t see the hail of stone crashing down. What he did see, after wiping the dust from his eyes, was the awesome sight of Minting Rock split in half like a geode.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Before his shock could even register, the opposite half began to fall away. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Fearful screams split the air as those Ayramun caught on the wrong side of Minting Rock grasped their impending doom. One of the Ayramun, his face sodden with dust, came leaping out of a tunnel in the opposite face. Mandri watched as he flew across the widening gap, but his flailing arms never found purchase, and the man fell screaming into the dust.}
