\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Mandri peered down from his blessed perch at the chaos, wind tousling his hair. A good number of Hrkan troops had been crushed under the undone half of Minting Rock. No doubt some Ayramun were buried down there as well. He couldn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t see clearly through the swirling smoke, but he could see a swarm of white Hrkan cloaks, and a sprinkling of black Ayramun rags. A yell rang out and these two blood rushed each other. The battle was once again joined.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Mandri looked to his left and right - there was no clear way to get down. He would have to climb. Then he thought better of it. He thought that, perhaps, it was best to be stuck up in a hole as high as he was. No matter who won, he\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92d be safe. He laid back down and tried to cut, when heard the familiar sound of the chisel chipping away at what was left of Minting Rock.}
